1. AuthenticationManager => Authentication Provider like InMemory, Our Own, LDAP and so on
2. configure(HttpWala) => Here we give permissions and roles to URI
3. Our own repository
4. Our Beans for fetching the user details from DB
5. Bean which Spring will need to authenticate the user
6. /authenticate service which will authenticate and return the JWT token
7. JWT toekn helper
8. JWT prefilter to validate token autheticity